<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIDEAST OIL AND U.S. TROOPS IN SAUDI ARABIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There is much talk about car-pooling and rapid transit. These are certainly 
important considerations in the desire to reduce our dependence on foreign oil. 
</P>
<P>
But everyone cannot participate in these programs. There is, however, one way 
in which every driver can assist in reducing our dependence on foreign oil. I 
have made a personal effort to hold down my top speed by 5 miles per hour and 
to eliminate rapid acceleration and braking. With just this simple effort, I 
have improved my mileage from 28 to 30 miles per gallon. 
</P>
<P>
To the average driver, this may mean an additional driving time of five minutes 
each way. This is not much of a hardship to see our soldiers return from Arab 
lands and to put people like Hussein in his place. 
</P>
<P>
ROCKY JAMES, Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
