<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To War or Not to War: ABC said Monday that it is planning a TV debate on the 
question of whether the United States should go to war against Iraq. The 
special edition of "Nightline" will be broadcast Dec. 7 at 11:30 p.m., 
continuing as long as it is deemed necessary, a network spokeswoman said. Ted 
Koppel will moderate the discussion among current and former government leaders 
and an audience of about 700 people at George Mason University near Washington, 
D.C. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112890-0040 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 314392 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 28, 1990, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
