<P>
Beached: ABC's critically acclaimed Vietnam War series "China Beach" has been 
placed on hiatus, the network announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
However, a network spokesman said the series will remain in production and will 
return to the schedule later this season. An announcement about a replacement 
series is expected later this week. "The Company" which stars Anthony Denison 
and Linda Purl as CIA agents trying to strike a balance between their marriage 
and jobs, is a favorite to replace "China Beach." BETH KLEID 
