<HEADLINE>
<P>
KARPOV, KASPAROV AGREE TO A DRAW, ARE TIED AT 7 POINTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LYON, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defending champion Gary Kasparov and challenger Anatoly Karpov agreed to a draw 
Tuesday in the 14th game of the World Chess Championship, leaving them 
deadlocked with seven points each. 
</P>
<P>
The game had adjourned Monday night with Kasparov sealing his 41st move, Qc2. 
</P>
<P>
Both had three pawns, a rook, a queen and king left. Without resuming play 
Tuesday, Karpov accepted Kasparov's offer of a draw. Game 15 is scheduled for 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Here are the moves of the 14th game: 
</P>
<P>
Kasparov-Karpov 14: 1 e4 e5 2 Nf3 Nc6 3 d4 exd4 4 Nxd4 Nf6 5 Nxc6 bxc6 6 e5 Qe7 
7 Qe2 Nd5 8 c4 Ba6 9 b3 0-0-0 10 g3 Re8 11 Bb2 f6 12 Bg2 fxe5 13 0-0 h5 14 Qd2 
Nf6 15 Qa5 Bb7 16 Ba3 Qe6 17 Bxf8 Rhxf8 18 Qxa7 Qg4 19 Na3 h4 20 Nc2 h3 21 Bh1 
Ne4 22 a4 Nc3 23 Rae1 Ne2+ 24 Rxe2 Qxe2 25 Nb4 d5 26 cxd5 cxd5 27 Bxd5 Bxb5 28 
Nxd5 Qc2 29 Qa6+ Kd7 30 Ne3 Qe4 31 Rc1 Rb8 32 Qf1 Rxb3 33 Qxh3+ Kd8 34 Qh5 Kc8 
35 Qd1 Rxe3 36 fxe3 Qxe3 37 Kh1 Qe4+ 38 Kg1 Qe3+ 39 Kh1 Qe4+ 40 Kg1 Rd8. Game 
adjourned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
