<HEADLINE>
<P>
NGUYEN VAN TAM; FORMER VIETNAM PRIME MINISTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nguyen Van Tam, 97, prime minister to former Vietnamese emperor Bao Dai. 
</P>
<P>
Nguyen was president of the Vietnamese Council from 1952-53 after holding 
several ministerial posts beginning in 1946. He was nicknamed the Tiger of Cai 
Lay for eliminating communist Vietnamese resistance groups in the Cai Lay 
region of the Mekong Delta. Named chief of criminal investigations in Saigon in 
1950, he put an end to a series of assassination attempts by the communist 
resistance. Nguyen obtained French nationality in 1927 and was awarded several 
decorations by the French government, including commander of the Legion of 
Honor. On Friday in Paris, where he had lived in exile since 1965. 
</P>
</TEXT>
