<P>
Food Inflation Seen Dipping in 1991: The Agriculture Department forecast that 
food prices will rise 2 to 5% in 1991, a return to more moderate levels of 
inflation after two years of increases in the range of 6%. 
</P>
<P>
The forecast suggested that food prices might return to the stable levels of 
the mid-1980s, when year-to-year increases were a modest 2% or 3%. Food prices 
are projected to rise 6% this year. Last winter's freeze in the South drove up 
fruit and vegetable prices. 
</P>
