<TEXT>
<P>
Possible AIDS Treatment Tested on Humans: Genentech, a South San Francisco 
biotechnology firm, said a small pilot study was begun last week at Walter Reed 
Institute of Research in Washington with "gp120," a potential immune system 
booster for those already infected with the AIDS virus. The drug being studied 
is a recombinant form of gp120, which is an exact copy, made through 
biotechnology, of a major protein on the surface of the virus that causes AIDS. 
"This study is the beginning of what could be a very long process, with an 
outcome that is uncertain," said Arthur J. Ammann, Genentech's director of 
clinical research. 
