<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUELAS WINS STATE FEATHERWEIGHT TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICH TOSCHES, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rafael Ruelas of Arleta won the state featherweight championship Tuesday night 
by stopping Richard Abila of Los Angeles in the seventh round of a scheduled 
12-round fight at the Country Club in Reseda. 
</P>
<P>
Ruelas, 19, ran his record to 22-0 with his 19th knockout. 
</P>
<P>
It was the first time he fought for a title. 
</P>
<P>
Ruelas knocked Abila down midway into the seventh round with a straight left 
and the referee stopped the fight. Ruelas dominated the fight, winning each 
round easily as Abila (16-7) threw few punches and didn't land many. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, former middleweight contender Alex Ramos, a New Yorker living in Simi 
Valley, weathered a severe beating early in the fifth round and stopped Roberto 
Rosiles at the end of the round. 
</P>
<P>
It was Ramos' second victory in two fights since a two-year layoff. A member of 
the 1980 U.S. Olympic team, he spent more than 20 months in state prison on an 
assault conviction. 
</P>
<P>
He was taking a pounding in the fifth when he landed a right under Rosiles' 
left ear and followed it with a right to the body. 
</P>
<P>
Rosiles went down from the second punch. After the bell, his handlers asked the 
ringside doctor to stop the fight. 
</P>
<P>
Ramos is 30-8-2. Rosiles, of Mexicali, Mexico, is 21-12-1. 
</P>
<P>
In another preliminary bout, heavyweight Rocky Pepeli of Burbank, knocked down 
by a left hook to the chin in the second round, came back to stop William 
Morris of Ontario in the third round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
