<P>
HEADING BACK: Three minutes after election of Britain's new prime minister 
(A1), Sir Eldon Griffiths (above) was phoning Orange County, saying he'll be 
back here by Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Griffiths, a Conservative member of Parliament from Suffolk and president of 
Orange County's World Affairs Council, was recalled to London to vote for prime 
minister. . . . The result seems "very brutal, but it is very efficient. In two 
weeks, we changed from a longstanding prime minister who was getting into 
trouble to a man who has the support of the entire party. If you have a 
President who falls out of favor, you're stuck with him." Jerry Hicks and 
