<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROOF FIRE CAUSES $100,000 IN DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FOUNTAIN VALLEY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A house sustained extensive damage to its roof Tuesday after sparks from the 
fireplace flew up the chimney and started the fire. 
</P>
<P>
Damage was estimated at $100,000. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters were called to the San Andres Street home after a neighbor alerted 
the home's owner, Joseph Newberry, that his roof was on fire. 
</P>
<P>
Sparks hit the shingle roofs of two other homes, but no serious damage was 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was extinguished within half an hour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
