<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-LOS ALAMITOS STAR EARNS PAC-10 HONOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
University of California volleyball player Cara Dane, a former standout at Los 
Alamitos High School, was named Pacific 10 Conference freshman of the year 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Dane, a 6-foot-2 middle blocker, set the school's single-season kill record 
with 152 this season for the Golden Bears. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
HONORS; VOLLEYBALL -- WOMEN; COLLEGE ATHLETICS; UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA AT 
BERKELEY 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
