<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCCONATHY AND BATES MAKE COLLEGE CHOICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cypress College's Doug McConathy has signed a letter of intent to play baseball 
at USC, and teammate Jason Bates has signed with Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
McConathy, a sophomore infielder from Western High School, batted .400 with 
eight home runs and 41 runs batted in during his freshman season at Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
Bates, a sophomore infielder from Esperanza, hit .272 with four home runs and 
25 RBI last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
