<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST WINS, ADVANCES TO STATE VOLLEYBALL TOURNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golden West College advanced to the state volleyball tournament by defeating 
Southwestern, 15-5, 15-3, 15-9, in a second-round Southern California Regional 
match at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West (21-3), ranked second in the state behind De Anza, was led by Kysha 
Green's 12 kills and five blocks. 
</P>
<P>
Joli Eberhart had 10 kills and seven digs and Brenda Irby had six kills, nine 
digs and five aces for Golden West, which won the match in only 52 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
Three of Irby's aces came in the third game during which Golden West came back 
from a 7-0 deficit to win. Southwestern finishes the season 14-4. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West next plays Hancock College at 8 p.m. Friday in Santa Maria. 
</P>
<P>
In women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 72, Santa Barbara 65 -- Cheryl Henderson and Latanya Trotter 
each scored 19 points to lead Rancho Santiago. Henderson also had 11 rebounds 
for Rancho Santiago (4-3), which trailed early in the second half. Heather 
Frowiss had 33 points and 18 rebounds for Santa Barbara. 
</P>
<P>
Chaffey 46, Orange Coast 45 -- Chrissy Sweeney, who scored 17 points, made one 
of two free throws with 38 seconds left to lift visiting Chaffey (5-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
