STUN GUN USED IN O.C. ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men shocked a Huntington Beach woman with an electric stun gun before 
robbing her of her purse, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Alicia K. Derieux, 23, told police that the robbers escaped with $1 in cash 
along with her checks and credit cards. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a rare one," Lt. John Foster said of the stun gun robbery. 
</P>
<P>
Stun guns, which are legal, send out electronic charges from two metal prongs, 
shocking the victim and in some cases rendering the person unconscious. 
</P>
<P>
The robbery occurred late last night at Derieux's carport at an apartment 
complex in the 6700 block of Warner Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Foster said two men approached Derieux and instructed her "not to turn around." 
</P>
<P>
"One of the suspects shot the woman (with the stun gun) in her right arm," 
Foster said. 
</P>
<P>
Derieux suffered a small bruise but she did not require hospitalization, Foster 
said. 
</P>
