COOPER TO LEAD ITALIAN SOUTH ALL-STAR TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NBA is holding a reunion in Rome on Saturday. It's called the Italian 
League All-Star Game. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Cooper, Darryl Dawkins and Darren Daye were among the group of some 20 
former NBA players selected for Italy's annual showcase for foreign stars. 
</P>
<P>
Cooper was the leading vote-getter in balloting by fans for the south squad. He 
is averaging 17 points and seven rebounds per game for Messaggero, which is 
tied for second place with a 9-3 record. 
</P>
<P>
Cooper won five NBA titles with the Lakers but never made the league's all-star 
team. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a great honor making the all-stars no matter what league you're in," 
Cooper said. "I feel guilty that after being in the so-called elite of 
basketball for so long it took me such such a short time to become an all-star 
here." 
</P>
<P>
Ex-Sacramento King Vinny Del Negro, who led all vote-getters, was nursing an 
ankle injury. 
</P>
