<P>
COLEMAN HOSPITALIZED IN ARIZONA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former child actor Gary Coleman, the star of television's "Diff'rent Strokes" 
series, has been hospitalized in Arizona with kidney problems, his publicist 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
"It is anticipated that the actor, who is resting comfortably and in good 
spirits, will be released from the hospital within a week's time," said Coleman 
spokesman Michael Gerety. 
</P>
<P>
Coleman lives in Tucson, but his exact whereabouts were secret. The publicist 
wouldn't reveal the name of the hospital or even the Arizona city where he was 
bedridden. 
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old actor was stable and "is expected to make a complete recovery," 
Gerety said. 
</P>
<P>
The exact nature of Coleman's ailment wasn't revealed, but his publicist said 
in a statement: "Coleman, the recipient of two kidney transplants, has a 
longstanding history of renal disease and his hospitalization is related to his 
kidney condition." 
</P>
</TEXT>
